          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1360.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1360.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook your cod </strong></p>\n<p>Meanwhile, return the pan to a medium heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong>.</p>\n<p>Pat the <strong>cod</strong> dry and season with a little <strong>salt</strong>.</p>\n<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>cod</strong> and cook for 2 minutes on each side or until deeply golden.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>cod</strong> to the baking<span class=\"text-highlight\"> tray next</span> to the <strong>coppa</strong>, and put it in the oven for 5 minutes further.</p>\n<p>Once done, remove the tray from the oven and leave to rest in a warm place.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1360.-step-4-x200.jpg",
