            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Start cooking your sauce</strong></p>\n<p>Give the pan a wipe with kitchen paper and return it to a medium heat. </p>\n<p>Once hot, add 15g<span class=\"text-danger\"> [30g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> with 10g <span class=\"text-danger\">[20g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir for 2 minutes until a paste is formed. </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for 30 seconds.</p>\n<p>Gradually whisk the<strong> chicken stock</strong> into the paste, a little at a time. Cook for 4 minutes or until a smooth, thick sauce remains.</p>",
